Facsimile Simulation/Emulation Library

  The <Facsimile> project's goal is to develop and maintain a high-quality, 3D,
  physics-enabled, discrete-event simulation/emulation library that can be used
  for industrial simulation and emulation projects in an engineering and/or
  manufacturing environment.

  <Facsimile> simulations run on <Microsoft> <Windows XP> and <Vista> as well
  as on <Linux>, <BSD> and <Unix>.

  <Facsimile> is open-source/free software and is distributed under version 3
  of the {{{http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html}GNU General Public License}}
  (GPLv3).

  If you would like to contribute to the Facsimile project, please visit the
  project's {{{http://www.facsim.org/}main site}} for further details.
